de.purpose: Dient der Darstellung von einzelnen Ergebniswerten fr Labor-Analyten, die in der klinischen Diagnostikanalyse wie medizinische Biochemie, Hmatologie, Immunologie und Transfusionsmedizin zu finden ist.
de.use:
Dient zur Erfassung von einzelnen Ergebniswerten fr Labor-Analyten, die in der klinischen Diagnostik verbreitet sind, wie z. B. biochemische, hmatologische, immunologische und transfusionsmedizinische Tests. Diese knnen auch in anatomisch-pathologischen Berichten als "zustzliche Untersuchungen" vorkommen.
 
Eine oder mehrere Instanzen dieses Archetyps knnen im SLOT "Testergebnis" des Archetyps OBSERVATION.laboratory_test_result verschachtelt werden.

Unter Umstnden kann dieser Archetyp in einem CLUSTER.laboratory_test_panel Archetyp verwendet werden - zusammen mit andere Analyten, die normalerweise als Teil eine Panels oder Profils getestet und/oder befundet werden.

Dieser Archetyp kann im Rahmen einer komplexerem Labor/Pathologie-Befundung, z.B. in anatomisch-pathologischen Befunden verwendet werden, in denen oft quantitative Resultate, wie Durchfluss-Zytometrie-Analysen neben den blichen makroskopischen und mikroskopischen Ergebnissen dokumentiert werden.
de.misuse:
Nicht zur Darstellung von makroskopischen / mikroskopischen Befunde in der anatomischen Pathologie zu verwenden, auer fr zustzliche Tests wie durchfluzytometrischen Studien.

Nicht zur Darstellung von Ergebnissen fr Mikrobiologische Befunde verwenden.

sv.purpose: Registrering av ett enskilt laboratorieanalysresultat som vanligtvis frekommer i underskningar inom exempelvis medicinsk biokemi, hematologi, immunologi och transfusionsmedicin.
sv.use:
Anvnds fr registrering av ett enskilt laboratorieresultat inom omrden ssom medicinsk biokemi, hematologi, immunologi och transfusionsmedicin. Arketypen kan ven anvndas fr kompletterande underskningar.

En eller flera instanser av denna arketyp kan nstlas i den SLOT fr "Underskningsresultat" som finns i arketypen OBSERVATION.laboratory_test_result. 

I vissa sammanhang kan denna arketyp anvndas i arketypen CLUSTER.laboratory_test_panel tillsammans med andra analyser som vanligtvis utfrs eller rapporteras tillsammans som en del av en analysgrupp, -paket eller -panel.

Denna arketyp kan anvndas i mer komplexa laboratorie- och patologirapporter dr kvantitativa svar ssom fldescytometri rapporteras tillsammans med konventionella makroskopiska och mikroskopiska underskningar.
sv.misuse:
Ska inte anvndas fr att registrera makroskopiska eller mikroskopiska patologifynd, frutom fr ytterligare underskningar ssom fldescytometri.

Ska inte anvndas fr att registrera mikrobiologiska resultat.

nb.purpose: For  registrere ett enkelt laboratorieresultat innenfor omrder som medisinsk biokjemi, hematologi, immunologi og transfusjonsmedisin.
nb.use:
For  registrere ett enkelt laboratorieresultat innenfor omrder som medisinsk biokjemi, hematologi, immunologi og transfusjonsmedisin. Arketypen kan ogs brukes til tilleggsunderskelser innenfor patologi.

En eller flere instanser av denne arketypen kan nstes i SLOTet "Underskelsesresultat" i arketypen OBSERVATION.laboratory_test_result.

I noen sammenhenger kan denne arketypen brukes i arketypen CLUSTER.laboratory_test_panel, sammen med andre analytter som vanligvis utfres sammen som del av en analysegruppe.

Denne arketypen kan brukes innenfor mer komplekse laboratorie/patologirapporter der kvantitative svar som for eksempel flowcytometri rapporteres sammen med konvensjonelle makroskopiske og mikroskopiske underskelser.
nb.misuse:
Skal ikke brukes til  registrere funn ved patologiunderskelser, annet enn for tilleggsunderskelser som flowcytometri.

Skal ikke brukes til  registrere mikrobiologiske dyrkningssvar.

pt-br.purpose: Para gravar valores nicos e individuais de resultados laboratoriais de analitos comuns a testes patolgicos clnicos como bioqumica, hematologia e imunologia.
pt-br.use:
Para gravar valores nicos e individuais de resultados laboratoriais de analitos comuns a testes patolgicos clnicos como bioqumica, hematologia e imunologia. Normalmente usados conjuntamente com o arqutipo parental OBSERVATION.laboratory_test_result e em algumas circunstncias ser carregado dentro de um arqutipo CLUSTER.laboratory_test_panel, junto com outros analitos que so normalmente testados e/ou reportados como parte de uma bateria, painel e perfil, embora no seja necessrio e.e mltiplos analitos podem ser carregados diretamente dentro do OBSERVATION.laboratory_test.

O atributo do nome do elemento "Resultado do analito"  normalmente substitudo em uma especializao, template ou em tempo de execuo para carregar o nome do analito especfico, p.e., "hemoglobina", frequentemente codificado com uma terminologia de referncia como LOINC, SNOMED CT ou NPU.

Este arqutipo pode ser usado dentro do contexto de relatrios laboratoriais/de patologia mais complexos como em relatrios de histopatologia/anatomia onde resultados quantitativos como de estudos de citometria de fluxo e testes genticos so frequentemente reportados junto com relatrios macroscpicos e microscpicos convencionais.
pt-br.misuse:
*Not to be used to record anatomical pathology macroscopic/microscopic findings, other than for additional testing such as cytometric flow studies.

Not to be used to record results for microbiological culture findings. (en)

en.purpose: To record a single value laboratory analyte result, commonly found in clinical pathology testing such as medical biochemistry, haematology, immunology and transfusion medicine.
en.use:
Use to record a single value laboratory analyte result, commonly found in clinical pathology testing such as medical biochemistry, haematology, immunology and transfusion medicine. They may also be found in anatomical pathology reports as 'ancillary tests'.

One or more instances of this archetype may be nested within the 'Test result' SLOT in the OBSERVATION.laboratory_test_result. 

In some circumstances this archetype may be carried within a CLUSTER.laboratory_test_panel archetype, together with other analytes which are normally tested and/or reported as part of a battery, panel or profile. 

This archetype may be used within the setting of more complex laboratory/pathology reporting such as anatomical pathology reports where quantitative results such as cytometric flow studies are often reported alongside conventional macroscopic and microscopic reporting.
en.misuse:
Not to be used to record anatomical pathology macroscopic/microscopic findings, other than for additional testing such as cytometric flow studies.

Not to be used to record results for microbiological culture findings.

Nicht zur Darstellung von makroskopischen / mikroskopischen Befunde in der anatomischen Pathologie zu verwenden, auer fr zustzliche Tests wie durchfluzytometrischen Studien.

Normalmente usados conjuntamente com o arqutipo parental OBSERVATION.laboratory_test_result e em algumas circunstncias ser carregado dentro de um arqutipo CLUSTER.laboratory_test_panel, junto com outros analitos que so normalmente testados e/ou reportados como parte de uma bateria, painel e perfil, embora no seja necessrio e.e mltiplos analitos podem ser carregados diretamente dentro do OBSERVATION.laboratory_test.

O atributo do nome do elemento "Resultado do analito"  normalmente substitudo em uma especializao, template ou em tempo de execuo para carregar o nome do analito especfico, p.e., "hemoglobina", frequentemente codificado com uma terminologia de referncia como LOINC, SNOMED CT ou NPU.

Este arqutipo pode ser usado dentro do contexto de relatrios laboratoriais/de patologia mais complexos como em relatrios de histopatologia/anatomia onde resultados quantitativos como de estudos de citometria de fluxo e testes genticos so frequentemente reportados junto com relatrios macroscpicos e microscpicos convencionais.

en.purpose: To record a single value laboratory analyte result, commonly found in clinical pathology testing such as medical biochemistry, haematology, immunology and transfusion medicine.
en.use:
Use to record a single value laboratory analyte result, commonly found in clinical pathology testing such as medical biochemistry, haematology, immunology and transfusion medicine. They may also be found in anatomical pathology reports as 'ancillary tests'.

One or more instances of this archetype may be nested within the 'Test result' SLOT in the OBSERVATION.laboratory_test_result. 

In some circumstances this archetype may be carried within a CLUSTER.laboratory_test_panel archetype, together with other analytes which are normally tested and/or reported as part of a battery, panel or profile. 

This archetype may be used within the setting of more complex laboratory/pathology reporting such as anatomical pathology reports where quantitative results such as cytometric flow studies are often reported alongside conventional macroscopic and microscopic reporting.
en.misuse:
Not to be used to record anatomical pathology macroscopic/microscopic findings, other than for additional testing such as cytometric flow studies.

Not to be used to record results for microbiological culture findings.

at0001.1.description: The value of the analyte result.
at0001.1.comment: For example '7.3 mmol/l', 'Raised'. The 'Any' data type will need to be constrained to an appropriate data type in a specialisation, a template or at run-time to reflect the actual analyte result. The Quantity data type has reference model attributes that include flags for normal/abnormal, reference ranges and approximations - see https://specifications.openehr.org/releases/RM/latest/data_types.html#_dv_quantity_class for more details.
